track_notes:
Arrive at Rhyd Ddu by WHR steam train for a good day out! Head into the village, noting the location of the cafe for later (mention me to Emma & Meno!). 
My route starts from near the pub. Head through the forest, being careful not to miss the little fork to the left at SH563541. There are a couple of pretty steep sections, but otherwise it is quite comfortable.

Track starts just north of WHR halt off A4085. Turn off track at sign, uphill into woods, slightly south of indicated PRoW on OS map. Follow obvious path emerging onto mountain side. Follow contour to meet path from Y Fron - turn straight up the mountain. Unrelenting climb to top, but good ground conditions.

This is the easiest way up Mynydd Mawr.
Rough parking spot at SH51615512 has room for 3+ cars. Follow farm lane to the common and then obvious tracks.
77 minutes up, 47 minutes down.

Total time (including ops): 5hr 0m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Mynydd Mawr Linear from Rhyd Ddu. May 2019.
